      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا اَلْحَسَنِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ طَيْرِ اَلْمَاءِ مِمَّا يَأْكُلُ اَلسَّمَكَ مِنْهُ يَحِلُّ قَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ كُلْهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4148 - Safwan ibn Yahya narrated from Muhammad ibn al-Harith who said: I asked Abu al-Hasan (as) about water birds that eat fish, whether they are permissible to eat.\nHe (as) said: \"There is no harm in it, eat them.\""
        ]
